The evidence with the title 'How health insurance marketplace plans set your premiums ... ' says Age: premiums can be up to 3 times higher for older people than for younger ones . Location: where you live has a big effect on your premiums. Differences in competition , state and local rules, and cost of living account for this. Tobacco use: insurers can charge tobacco users up to 50 % more than those who don't use  ... 
